did.unittitle: Washington Metropolitan Area Transit Authority: Metro History Project Collection
did.abstract: Collection contains correspondence, clippings, transcripts of speeches and Congressional hearings, bound volumes, cassette tapes, and maps that document the history of the development of rapid transit facilities for the Washington metropolitan area. The records date from 1930 to 1984.

prefercite.head: Preferred citation

bioghist.head: Historical or Biographical Note
bioghist.p: The Metro History Project was a project of Metro 2001, Inc., an organization founded in 1979 to produce a book-length history of the Metro for the Washington Metropolitan Transit Authority. Using documents obtained from local archives and private collections, Metro 2001, Inc. produced several short works entitled "Metro History Monographs." Although many of these documents were cataloged and entered into a database to be indexed, the book was never completed and the project was abandoned. The materials were donated to The George Washington University in 1985. Related material can be found in the papers of C. Darwin Stolzenbach.

scopecontent.head: Collection Scope and Content
scopecontent.p: This collection contains correspondence, clippings, transcripts of speeches and Congressional hearings, bound volumes, cassette tapes, and maps that document the history of the development of rapid transit facilities for the Washington metropolitan area. The records date from 1930 to 1984.

Because the numbering system assigned to the items does not reflect chronological or alphabetical order, the Project's indexes should be consulted first. These include a document index, a photograph index, an index of proposed chapters to never-completed book, and a Global Index. The oral history transcripts are often incomplete or paraphrased, so they should only be used for overview purposes. The tapes contain the complete original interviews.

arrangement.head: Collection Organization
arrangement.p: Organized into five series: Historical documents, Photograph file lists, Publications, Oral histories, and Oversized documents.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents note
scopecontent.p: This series, representing the largest portion of the collection, contains documents including Congressional hearings, correspondence, and clippings dating from 1930 to 1984. It also contains an index of the documents.

scopecontent.p: This series contains indexes to 491 photogaphs housed at the WMATA. The lists index the images by year, line number, name, place, and subject.

scopecontent.p: This series contains indexes for each proposed chapter of the Metro History Project book, broken down by type of index. Copies of the monographs resulting from the Metro History Project are also included.
